<Vertical id="TabsDemo" title="Tabs Block Demo" launchable="true">

  <Markdown>
# Tabs Block Demo

The Tabs block creates a tabbed interface where each child block becomes a tab panel.
Tab labels come from the child's `label` or `title` attribute.
  </Markdown>

  <Tabs id="demo_tabs">
    <Vertical id="tab_first" label="First Tab">
      <Markdown>
## First Tab Content

This is the content of the first tab. You can include any blocks here.
      </Markdown>
      <LineInput id="tab1_input" placeholder="Input in first tab"/>
    </Vertical>

    <Vertical id="tab_second" label="Second Tab">
      <Markdown>
## Second Tab Content

This is the content of the second tab.
      </Markdown>
      <TextArea id="tab2_textarea" placeholder="Text area in second tab"/>
    </Vertical>

    <Vertical id="tab_third" title="Third Tab">
      <Markdown>
## Third Tab Content

Note: Both `label` and `title` attributes work for tab names.
      </Markdown>
    </Vertical>
  </Tabs>

  <Markdown>
## Interactive Example

Tabs can contain interactive components that maintain state independently.
  </Markdown>

  <Tabs id="interactive_tabs">
    <Vertical id="activity_tab" label="Activity">
      <Markdown>
Enter your response below:
      </Markdown>
      <LineInput id="activity_input" placeholder="Your answer..."/>
    </Vertical>

    <Vertical id="notes_tab" label="Notes">
      <TextArea id="notes_area" placeholder="Take notes here..."/>
    </Vertical>
  </Tabs>

</Vertical>
